By Dorcas Elusogbon Ile-Ife (Osun) –   An Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun on Monday remanded one Mathew Omoniyi, 22, in police custody over alleged theft of a television and wrist watches. The Prosecutor, Insp Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on April 11, 2019, at about 2:10 a.m at Ile-Ife. He said the defendant, of no fixed address, entered into the house of one Eze Sunday and carted away one 32-inch television, three wrist watches and one trouser belt, all valued at N70, 000. According to him, the offence contravened Sections 383, 390(9), 411 and 412 of the Criminal Code Laws of Osun, 2002. The defendant, who was not represented by a counsel, pleaded guilty to a three-count charge of intent to commit felony, entrance and stealing. Magistrate Muhibah Olatunji, who did not grant bail to the defendant, ordered his remand at ‘A’ Division Police Station at Moore, Ile-Ife. Olatunji adjourned the case till June 22 for presentation of facts. (NAN) By Dorcas Elusogbon Ile-Ife (Osun) - An Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun on Tuesday remanded two suspects, Ganiyu Taofeek and Olawuyi Busola at ‘A’ Division Police Station, Moore, Ile-Ife, over an alleged theft of N300,000. Taofeek, 27 and Busola, 19, are being tried for conspiracy and stealing The Prosecutor, Insp.… May 19, 2020 In "Metro" By Dorcas Elusogbon Ile-Ife (Osun) - An Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun, on Thursday, remanded one Lawrence Olajide, 26, in the Nigerian Correctional Service over alleged laptop theft. The defendant is facing a five-count charge of conspiracy, burglary, entering, stealing and robbery. The Prosecutor, Insp. Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that… November 14, 2019 In "Metro" By Dorcas Elusogbon Ile-Ife (Osun) - An Ile-Ife Magistrates’ Court in Osun on Wednesday ordered that one Ojo Adebayo should be remanded in police custody for allegedly stealing four cows. The Prosecutor, Insp. Emmanuel Abdullahi, told the court that Adebayo committed the 